Next: "People in more mature industries generally have a reasonable expectation what their careers would look like in say 20 years (and generally can expect salary to be monotonic-increasing)."

Issues: "have a reasonable expectation what their careers would look like" missing "of" or "that": should be "have a reasonable expectation of what their careers would look like" or "expect that". Also "monotonic-increasing" hyphen okay.

Next: "But I always knew we're in a state of flux."

